meanings: Adjective 손실[손해]이 난; 되찾을 수 없는, 놓쳐 버린
A very elite hacker who owns.

A conversation ender. Used at the end of a statement when a person in the middle of a conversation wishes to stop talking about it immediately. Coined from the TV show LOST, where at the end of every episode, the word "LOST" flashes across the screen, ending the episode very abruptly or on a clif...
